         <abstract>
            <p>For a plane polygonal domain Ω and a corresponding (general) triangulation we define classes of functions p&lt;sub&gt;m&lt;/sub&gt;(x, y) which are polynomials on each triangle and which are in C&lt;sup&gt;(m)&lt;/sup&gt;(Ω) and also belong to the Sobolev space W&lt;sup&gt;(m+1)&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;(Ω). Approximation theoretic properties are proved concerning these functions. These results are then applied to the approximate solution of arbitrary-order elliptic boundary value problems by the Galerkin method. Estimates for the error are given. The case of second-order problems is discussed in conjunction with special choices of approximating polynomials.</p>
          </abstract>
